<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1325,1268,1814]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The species is widely distributed from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[834,924,1268,1294]" name="Mexico" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1072,1148,1268,1294]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The nominate subspecies is not uncommon in 
<collectingCountry box="[637,761,1308,1334]" name="Venezuela" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, Northern 
<collectingCountry box="[885,960,1308,1334]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1066,1308,1334]" name="Guyana" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1077,1254,1308,1334]" name="French Guiana" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Suriname" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Surinam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[371,471,1348,1374]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[485,630,1348,1374]" pageId="12" pageNumber="16" refString="Miller, J. Y. (1986) The taxonomy, phylogeny, and zoogeography of the Neotropical Castniinae (Lepidoptera: Castnioidea: Castniidae). Ph. D. thesis. University of Florida, Gainesville, USA, 571 pp." type="book" year="1986">
Miller 
<number box="[567,630,1348,1374]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaye" box="[650,925,1348,1374]" pageId="12" pageNumber="16" refString="Kaye, W. J., Lamont, N. (1927) A catalogue of the Trinidad Lepidoptera Heterocera (Moths). Memoirs of the Department of Agriculture of Trinidad and Tobago, 3, 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1927">
Kaye &amp; Lamont (
<number box="[855,916,1348,1374]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1927.0">1927</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
list it from 
<collectingCountry box="[1061,1161,1348,1374]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
without comment. Typically, food plants of 
<taxonomicName box="[640,810,1388,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Xanthocastnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,810,1388,1413]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Xanthocastnia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1017,1125,1388,1413]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Bromelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1017,1125,1388,1413]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Bromelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1143,1311,1388,1414]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
), although some 
<taxonomicName box="[456,572,1428,1453]" class="Liliopsida" family="Heliconiaceae" genus="Heliconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zingiberales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,572,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Heliconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<taxonomicName box="[656,826,1428,1454]" class="Liliopsida" family="Heliconiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Heliconiaceae</taxonomicName>
) may also be used (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[1090,1240,1428,1454]" pageId="12" pageNumber="16" refString="Miller, J. Y. (1986) The taxonomy, phylogeny, and zoogeography of the Neotropical Castniinae (Lepidoptera: Castnioidea: Castniidae). Ph. D. thesis. University of Florida, Gainesville, USA, 571 pp." type="book" year="1986">
Miller 
<number box="[1179,1240,1428,1454]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moss" pageId="12" pageNumber="16" refString="Moss, A. M. (1945) The Castnia of Para, with notes on others (Lep. Castniidae). Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London (B), 14, 48 - 52." type="journal article" year="1945">
Moss 
<number box="[264,327,1468,1494]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1945.0">1945</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1325,1268,1814]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
In 
<collectingCountry box="[348,451,1508,1534]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[468,589,1508,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Castnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evalthe">
<emphasis box="[468,589,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">X. evalthe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found occasionally in the forests of the Northern Range. It has not been recorded from other parts of the island, but there seems little reason why it should not be more widespread. 
<collectionCode box="[729,814,1588,1614]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">MJWC</collectionCode>
has observed that it flies at a height of 
<quantity metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="m" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 m</quantity>
, within the forest, and does not normally frequent open ridge tops or hilltops.
</paragraph>
